<node id="B部門">
  <data key="d0">B部門</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-daa296a353c26f41dfc613743d24e936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942b136689124792272bc32a2898842c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf168eec40aae386455af5027929f6fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d96ca3133c54d9d76add7de434ee05b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7504d68fad10caa1cd0ea41314ed2ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3781d1671ca7126e99e7656264965fb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2940790b50eb2cba2a5e944b95a94dd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95280ea367581dac710f0dc56c7a72f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-333af5cc1ff286e512f36be66d1aa78b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f62a98ad02d11a4c9618cbda43281859&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ebe784b7ece61edcdd2e054763c0ce3</data>
  <data key="d2">B部門 is a department within B客戶 that is responsible for various maintenance-related tasks. The primary responsibilities of the B部門 include monitoring and managing indexing synchronization status by adding new indexers to the IDX cluster node, handling API requests for IP addresses, testing KVstore engines, and performing specific data collection activities related to FISAC. Additionally, this department plays a crucial role in troubleshooting issues involving n8n's connection to Splunk and participating in general maintenance work associated with Splunk.

On November 5, 2025, B部門 was specifically assigned certain maintenance tasks within the organization of B客戶. These tasks encompass both ongoing activities and specific assignments aimed at ensuring the smooth operation and continuous improvement of various systems and services under management.&lt;SEP&gt;B部门是进行另一些维护活动的组织单位。&lt;SEP&gt;B部門is another department involved in maintenance and configuration of Splunk systems.&lt;SEP&gt;B部門is a department handling ongoing tasks such as FISAC data collection and SH KVstore engine anomaly testing.</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773782810</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="C客戶">
  <data key="d0">C客戶</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Cお客様 is an organization or entity that serves as the recipient of maintenance services and for which maintenance records are systematically documented. Across multiple sources, Cお客様 is consistently described as both the client receiving maintenance services and the subject of maintenance record-keeping activities. These descriptions emphasize that Cお客様 engages in ongoing relationships with service providers who maintain detailed logs and documentation related to the upkeep, servicing, and support provided to the entity.

Cお客様 specifically refers to an organization for which maintenance records are meticulously kept. The maintenance performed includes various services such as upkeep, servicing, and support, all of which are carefully documented by the service providers. This process ensures that there is a comprehensive record of all activities related to maintaining Cお客様's operational standards and integrity.&lt;SEP&gt;C客戶is the client for whom maintenance records are being kept.&lt;SEP&gt;C客戶is a client for whom maintenance records are kept.&lt;SEP&gt;C客戶is an organization for which maintenance records are kept.</data>
