  <data key="d2">World Athletics Federation is an organization that oversees various aspects of global athletics, including major events such as the World Athletics Championships. It plays a crucial role in managing and verifying record validations to maintain the integrity and accuracy of athletic performances worldwide. The federation ensures that achievements like new world records are officially recognized during significant athletic competitions it governs. Additionally, it is responsible for overseeing the rules and regulations for these global athletics events, ensuring consistency and fairness across all competitions under its purview.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees global athletics events like the World Athletics Championship.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees global athletic competitions and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the World Athletics Championship and validates new records.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees global athletics events like the World Athletics Championship and validates records.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the World Athletics Championship and validates records.</data>
