<edge source="Noah Carter" target="World Athletics Federation">
  <data key="d7">32.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The World Athletics Federation is responsible for overseeing the conduct, performance standards, and record validations for athletes such as Noah Carter during championship events. This organization plays a critical role in ensuring fair competition and adherence to established norms and procedures. Specifically, it validates athletic achievements and new world records set by athletes like Carter, including his recent 100m sprint record.

The World Athletics Federation ensures transparency and integrity within competitive athletics by verifying that athletes' performances meet the stringent criteria set forth for record validation. It oversees both the conduct of participating athletes and the official recognition of any new world records they achieve at championships. This includes maintaining oversight over the rules and regulations under which Carter competes to ensure compliance with guidelines established by the federation.

Furthermore, the World Athletics Federation maintains a crucial role in overseeing the competition in which Noah Carter set his new record, ensuring that all performances meet established standards for validation. The organization's responsibilities extend beyond just validation; it also plays a part in managing the overall conduct and performance expectations of athletes during championship events.

The World Athletics Federation oversees the rules and regulations for athletes competing in various events such as Noah Carter's championship races. Its role is integral to verifying records set by athletes like Carter at major championships, thereby guaranteeing the authenticity of these achievements within the sporting community. Additionally, it ensures that all new records are officially recognized and adhering to stipulated norms and procedures, thus maintaining a high level of integrity in competitive athletics.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the validation of athletic achievements like Noah Carter's new record.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation validates and recognizes the new record set by Noah Carter at the championship.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees record validations for athletes like Noah Carter who set new records.</data>
  <data key="d9">athlete achievement,athlete compliance,athlete governance,athlete oversight,athlete recognition,athlete regulation,athlete supervision,athletic achievement,competition oversight,governance,governing body,oversight,performance validation,record validation,regulation</data>
