<edge source="Market Selloff" target="Nexon Technologies">
  <data key="d7">10.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Market Selloff, Nexon Technologies refers to a significant event where the decline in Nexon Technologies' stock value contributed to an overall market selloff. This decline is influenced by multiple factors including broader concerns over rising interest rates and regulatory issues affecting the company and the entire market. Investor concerns over these economic conditions led to widespread selling pressure on Nexon Technologies’ shares, which in turn exacerbated the broader market downturn. Additionally, the stock decline was partially attributed to lower-than-expected quarterly earnings reported by Nexon Technologies, further contributing to investor uncertainty and the resultant sell-off. Overall, the significant drop in Nexon Technologies' stock price played a notable role in amplifying the extent of the market selloff during this period.&lt;SEP&gt;Nexon Technologies' stock decline was part of the broader market selloff due to investor concerns over interest rates and regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Nexon Technologies' stock decline contributed to the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns.</data>
  <data key="d9">company impact,earnings disappointment,index movement,investor concern,market reaction,regulatory uncertainty,specific performance</data>
